1 Just ice Pay for Success Revolving Fund, created in Section 510.8c of
2 Title 57 of the Oklahoma Statutes, and the sum of One Million Two
3 Hundred Thousand Dollars ($1,200,000.00) to the Pay for Success
4 Innovation Fund, created in Section 9010.5 of Title 62 of the
5 Oklahoma Statutes.
6 SECTION 2. Of the amount allocated for the Pay for Success
7 program in Section 1 of this act, seventy-five percent (75%) shall
8 be utilized by the Office of Management and Enterprise Services in
9 equal amounts for municipalities of the state with populations of
10 three hundred fifty thousand (350,000) or more as determined by the
11 latest Federal Decennial Census.
12 SECTION 3. There is hereby appropriated to the Central
13 Purchasing Contract Database Revolving Fund, established in Enrolled
14 House Bill No. 3415 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma
15 Legislature, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
16 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
17 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
18 ($500,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to carry out
19 the provisions of Enrolled House Bill No. 3415 of the 2nd Session of
20 the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
21 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
22 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
